The above two trends imply the similarity of BQs to the given MQ decreases from the first partition to the seventh partition (i.e., the noise level increases). Specifically, the level of noise increases from the first partition to the seventh because our assumption is that a BQ with smaller similarity score to the given MQ indicates that this BQ introduces more noise to the given MQ and vice versa.
